Package: fmlr
Type: Package
Title: Fused Matrix Library
Version: 0.2-0
Description: Interface to the 'fml' library, which defines a single
    "medium-level" interface for multiple dense matrix types (CPU, GPU, and
    MPI), each supporting multiple fundamental types (half, float, double). Data
    is held externally to R and operations that modify data generally occur
    in-place. The 'fmlr' interface largely tracks with the core 'fml' interface.
    We use R6 so that generally an R code can be easily translated to C++.
License: BSL-1.0
SystemRequirements: C++14, GNU make
Depends:
    R (>= 3.6.0),
    pbdMPI (>= 0.4-0),
    pbdSLAP (>= 0.3-0),
    float (>= 0.2-0)
Imports:
    R6 (>= 2.4.1)
LinkingTo:
    float (>= 0.2-0)
Suggests:
    memuse (>= 4.0-0),
    merkhet (>= 0.2-0)
ByteCompile: yes
Authors@R: c(
    person("Drew", "Schmidt", role=c("aut", "cre"), email="wrathematics@gmail.com")
    )
Maintainer: Drew Schmidt <wrathematics@gmail.com>
URL: https://github.com/fml-fam/fmlr
BugReports: https://github.com/fml-fam/fmlr/issues
RoxygenNote: 7.1.0
HPCRAN: blas, gpu, mpi
